                       Report Class Configuration Help           Page 1 of 4
 
      A report class is a logical grouping of statistical report
      codes which will be generated by the stations on the Distributed
      Network. The report class configuration is utilized to minimize
      the amount of information required for station configuration.
      This menu allows report class functions to be performed,
      including: adding, modifying, deleting, and listing report
      classes.
 
      Adding A Report Class
      =====================
      To add a report class to the Distributed Network, enter "1" (for
      Add Report Class), and press return.  The program will then prompt
      for the report class number.  Enter the class number and press
      return.  If the class already exists, an error message will be
      displayed, and you will be prompted for another class.  If the
      class does not exist, the Add a Report Class screen will be
      displayed, requiring the report class configuration to be input.
 
 
