      Deleting a Report Class (cont'd)
      ================================
      To delete a class, enter "3" and press return.  Enter the class
      number, and if it exists, the Delete a Class screen will be displayed.
      If the class does not exist, an error message will be displayed, and
      you must re-enter the number.  Once the Delete Screen has been
      displayed, look at the configuration information to ensure that this
      is the correct class.  If you wish to delete it, enter "Y" and press
      return, and a message will be displayed informing that the class
      was deleted.  If you no not wish to delete the class, enter "N" and
      the class will not be deleted.
 
      Listing Report Classes
      ======================
      This option will allow all report classes to be displayed.  The
      user also has the ability to scroll forward or back, to view the
      desired information.
 
      For more information refer to Report Class Listing help.
